<div id="review_3913726456" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3913726456" />
    <a title="LaDonna" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/4803142-ladonna"><img alt="LaDonna" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1459333265p2/4803142.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3913726456?book_show_action=true">Apr 26, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="LaDonna" class="user" itemprop="url" name="LaDonna" href="/user/show/4803142-ladonna">LaDonna</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4803142-ladonna?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4803142-ladonna?shelf=owned-paperback">owned-paperback</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4803142-ladonna?shelf=thrift-store-find">thrift-store-find</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/4803142-ladonna?shelf=true-crime">true-crime</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3913726456" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer12005016592723056279">Probably the most brutal and gruesome book I have ever read, and I read quite a bit of horror. As both a former criminal justice major and a former New Mexican, the entire story fascinates me. I first moved to NM in 85, just a few short years after the massacre. I remember mentions of it on the news from time to time, but, at 12, I was simply too young to truly comprehend any of it.<br/><br/>To someone not familiar with NM politics,a lot of the book will read more as fiction than reality. The author does </span>
  <span id="freeText12005016592723056279" style="display:none">Probably the most brutal and gruesome book I have ever read, and I read quite a bit of horror. As both a former criminal justice major and a former New Mexican, the entire story fascinates me. I first moved to NM in 85, just a few short years after the massacre. I remember mentions of it on the news from time to time, but, at 12, I was simply too young to truly comprehend any of it.<br /><br />To someone not familiar with NM politics,a lot of the book will read more as fiction than reality. The author does a fair job of not playing to any bias, but it was a horrific situation all the way around. This is a well researched book, and gives good insight into the horrors surrounding those 36 hours, what led up to it, and what didn't truly change after.<br /><br />As a former photographer I have wanted to do a photo tour there for years, but if I get the chance to sometime in the not too distant future I will definitely be going in with a much different mindset than I would have prior to having read this. I have long been enthralled with pictures I have seen taken of the gas chamber. Though I was aware of the riot, I didn't really have a true understanding of just how depraved it actually was. I'm positive after reading this that the gas chamber is far from being the most haunted part of the property. My desire to see it first hand hasn't changed, but my thoughts and feelings about the worst prison riot in history certainly have.</span>
  <a data-text-id="12005016592723056279" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


