<div id="review_2738069059" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2738069059" />
    <a title="sara" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/69981304-sara"><img alt="sara" src="https://s.gr-assets.com/assets/nophoto/user/u_50x66-632230dc9882b4352d753eedf9396530.png" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2738069059?book_show_action=true">Mar 08, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="sara" class="user" itemprop="url" name="sara" href="/user/show/69981304-sara">sara</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2738069059" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer4038779712972675362">Horrific but compelling historic read. It was like reading a true story horror film. Many lessons of leadership failure, combined with those of frightening ways human nature can unravel into chaos. At times it was hard to follow, but I think this is is because of the chaotic unfolding, limited outside witnesses and inside testimony to what went on. Although this event went on in New Mexico in 1980, it could happen anywhere and not only in the penal system. </span>

          </span>
        </div>


